OL,3,CDepartment of Health defends #188,000
OL,4,Csalary of new boss
OL,6,FThe Department of Health has defended
OL,7,Fthe #188,000 salary that will be paid
OL,8,Fto the man appointed to try and reform
OL,9,FNorthern Ireland's health service.
OL,11,FMike Farrar, a former high-ranking
OL,12,Fofficial in NHS England, has been
OL,13,Fannounced as the Department of
OL,14,FHealth's interim Permanent Secretary.
OL,16,FHis salary is higher than that of
OL,17,Fother departmental Permanent
OL,18,FSecretaries and even the head of the
OL,19,FCivil Service Dr Jayne Brady.
